        "canonical_link": null,
        "text": "For most people visiting Puglia, Brindisi is merely a point of arrival and departure, thanks to its being home to one of Puglia’s two main airports. But if you're staying in the area or are looking for somewhere to spend a few hours before catching your flight home, Brindisi is well worth a visit. Brindisi, with its rich tapestry of history, stunning coastal scenery, and warm hospitality, offers a unique travel experience. Brindisi's historical legacy is visible in its architecture, from ancient Roman columns to majestic Baroque churches and the formidable fortress of Emperor Frederick II. The city's recent revitalisation has breathed new life into its urban spaces, making it an inviting destination for both leisure and exploration."
